---
import MarketingLayout from "../../layouts/MarketingLayout.astro";
const lastUpdated = "May 11, 2026";
---

<MarketingLayout title="Terms of Service — Madar AI" description="The terms that govern your use of Madar AI.">
  <section class="pt-32 pb-24 px-6 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="text-[10px] font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-[#F97316] mb-3">Legal</div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-4">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="text-[11px] font-mono text-white/40">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-madar space-y-8">
      <section>
        <h2>1. Agreement</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your access to and use of Madar AI ("the Service"), operated by Zyrix Global Technologies ("Madar," "we," "us"). By creating an account or using the Service, you agree to be bound by these Terms. If you do not agree, do not use the Service.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>2. Eligibility</h2>
        <p>
          You must be at least 18 years old and have the legal capacity to enter into a binding contract to use Madar. If you are using the Service on behalf of a company, you represent that you have authority to bind that company to these Terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>3. Your Account</h2>
        <p>
          You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account credentials and for all activity under your account. Notify us immediately at <a href="mailto:security@madarai.co">security@madarai.co</a> if you suspect unauthorized access.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>4. The Service</h2>
        <p>
          Madar is an AI Growth Operating System that ingests data from third-party platforms you connect (such as App Store Connect, Google Play, RevenueCat, and AppsFlyer) and produces insights, forecasts, and recommendations. You grant Madar the rights necessary to access this data on your behalf for the purpose of operating the Service.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>5. Plans, Billing, and Refunds</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Pricing for each plan is published on our <a href="/pricing">pricing page</a>.</li>
          <li>Subscriptions renew automatically until canceled.</li>
          <li>You may cancel at any time from your account settings. Cancellations take effect at the end of the current billing period.</li>
          <li>Except where required by law, fees already paid are non-refundable.</li>
          <li>We may change pricing for future billing periods with at least 30 days' notice.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>6. Acceptable Use</h2>
        <p>You agree not to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Reverse-engineer, decompile, or attempt to extract the source code of the Service</li>
          <li>Use the Service to violate any law or third-party right</li>
          <li>Interfere with the integrity or performance of the Service</li>
          <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to other accounts or systems</li>
          <li>Use the Service to build a competing product</li>
          <li>Scrape or systematically extract data from the Service beyond what our APIs permit</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>7. AI Outputs</h2>
        <p>
          Madar's insights, forecasts, and recommendations are generated by machine learning models trained on historical data. They are decision-support tools, not financial, legal, or business advice. You remain solely responsible for any decisions you make based on the Service's output. Madar makes no guarantee that any forecast or recommendation will produce a specific outcome.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>8. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>
          The Service, including all software, models, designs, and content (excluding your data), is owned by Zyrix Global Technologies and protected by intellectual property laws. You retain all rights to the data you submit to the Service. You grant us a limited license to process that data solely to operate the Service.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>9. Confidentiality</h2>
        <p>
          Each party agrees to protect the other party's confidential information with at least the same degree of care it uses to protect its own confidential information. This obligation survives termination of these Terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>10. Termination</h2>
        <p>
          You may terminate your account at any time. We may suspend or terminate your account if you breach these Terms, if required by law, or if your use poses a security risk. On termination, your right to use the Service ends immediately. We will delete your data per our Privacy Policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>11. Disclaimers</h2>
        <p>
          The Service is provided "as is" and "as available," without warranties of any kind, whether express or implied, including warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and non-infringement. We do not warrant that the Service will be uninterrupted, error-free, or that any defects will be corrected.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>12. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          To the maximum extent permitted by law, Madar's total liability arising out of or related to these Terms or the Service will not exceed the amount you paid us in the 12 months preceding the event giving rise to the liability. In no event will Madar be liable for indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>13. Indemnification</h2>
        <p>
          You agree to indemnify and hold Madar harmless from any claim arising out of your use of the Service in violation of these Terms or applicable law.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>14. Governing Law</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms are governed by the laws of the Republic of Türkiye. Any dispute will be resolved in the courts of Istanbul, Türkiye, unless local consumer protection laws give you the right to sue in your own jurisdiction.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>15. Changes to These Terms</h2>
        <p>
          We may update these Terms from time to time. We will notify you of material changes by email or in-product notice at least 30 days before they take effect. Continued use of the Service after the changes take effect constitutes acceptance of the new Terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>16. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about these Terms? Email <a href="mailto:legal@madarai.co">legal@madarai.co</a>.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[11px] font-mono text-white/40 mt-6">
          Zyrix Global Technologies<br/>
          Istanbul, Türkiye
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style is:global>
    .prose-madar h2 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      color: white;
    }
    .prose-madar p {
      color: rgba(255,255,255,0.75);
      line-height: 1.75;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      font-size: 1rem;
    }
    .prose-madar ul, .prose-madar ol {
      color: rgba(255,255,255,0.75);
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      padding-left: 1.5rem;
    }
    .prose-madar ul li { list-style: disc; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; line-height: 1.7; }
    .prose-madar ol li { list-style: decimal; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; line-height: 1.7; }
    .prose-madar strong { color: white; font-weight: 600; }
    .prose-madar a { color: #F97316; text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 3px; }
    .prose-madar a:hover { color: #FB923C; }
  </style>
</MarketingLayout>